parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall - Parts Distribution Disconnect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace the Takata airbags in a timely manner can lead to serious injuries or fatalities due to the deployment of faulty airbags, which can cause metal fragments to be propelled towards the occupants.
symptoms: No symptoms are reported
as the issue is related to the recall repair process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: No airbags deployed in a crash
resulting in injuries to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete repair of the Takata airbag recall can lead to serious injuries or fatalities due to the deployment of faulty airbags.
symptoms: Incomplete repair of the recall
with some airbags not being replaced
and the dealer not providing a clear explanation of the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission or powertrain can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes loud noises or clunks
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the PTU can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, or becoming stuck in gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle leaks transmission fluid
the PTU makes loud noises or clunks
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the odometer or speedometer can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The odometer or speedometer displays incorrect or erratic readings
the vehicle's speedometer or odometer fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate suddenly, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly or unexpectedly
the vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become stiff or hard to press, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
there is a hissing or whistling noise when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor can cause the ABS, airbag, and check engine warning lights to remain illuminated, leading to reduced vehicle safety and potentially accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS
airbag
and check engine warning lights remain illuminated
the vehicle's brakes may lock up or become unresponsive
the vehicle's traction control system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to become stiff or hard to press, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
there is a hissing or whistling noise when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
